A tragic plane crash in Greece claimed the lives of all 121 passengers and crew members aboard a Helios Airways flight.
Angry relatives confronted airline officials at Larnaca airport, suspecting a technical fault as the cause.
Experts suggested a lack of oxygen may have incapacitated the crew, leading to the crash.
The aircraft's decompression issues raised concerns, with similarities drawn to past incidents.
Rescue efforts recovered black boxes for investigation, while authorities ruled out terrorism.
The aviation community remains puzzled by the rare occurrence of a crash due to depressurization.
